1
00:01:40,470 --> 00:01:45,930
[Speed and Love]

2
00:01:46,229 --> 00:01:48,830
[Episode 5]

3
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:53,910
Brandy!

4
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:57,140
Brandy, are you here?

5
00:01:58,420 --> 00:01:59,259
Brandy!

6
00:01:59,420 --> 00:02:00,670
Zhang, Zhang...

7
00:02:00,860 --> 00:02:01,670
Well,

8
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,780
B-Brandy went to the auto parts market.

9
00:02:03,780 --> 00:02:05,060
If you n-need anything,

10
00:02:05,060 --> 00:02:05,970
just feel free to tell me.

11
00:02:05,970 --> 00:02:06,700
Have a smoke.

12
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:09,539
Who are they?

13
00:02:09,710 --> 00:02:11,150
Who do you think you are?

14
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:13,750
Behave yourself.

15
00:02:13,820 --> 00:02:14,660
I've seen

16
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:16,640
-that yellow-haired man at the boxing gym.
-Brandy!

17
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:17,570
-That's him.
-Come out!

18
00:02:17,570 --> 00:02:19,500
-He Zhang from Wanji Garage.
-Come out and have fun!

19
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,340
Brandy!

20
00:02:20,470 --> 00:02:21,470
What do they want to do?

21
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:24,120
Brandy used to work at Wanji Garage
for a few years.

22
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,050
After he started his own business,

23
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:28,430
that man's been coming here to harass him.

24
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:31,150
Stay here.

25
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:36,560
Well, hello, Zhang.

26
00:02:37,590 --> 00:02:38,660
Long time no see.

27
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:42,620
But what's going on now?

28
00:02:43,270 --> 00:02:45,150
Taking advantage while the owner is away

29
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:47,340
and causing trouble, what does that prove?

30
00:02:47,340 --> 00:02:49,100
Those who know you might think
you're just fooling around.

31
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:50,060
But others

32
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:54,160
might think you're cowards
taking advantage of people.

33
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:56,020
We all work and live in this area.

34
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:58,220
It'll be embarrassing if word gets out.

35
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:00,280
It's none of your business.

36
00:03:00,710 --> 00:03:01,430
Get lost.

37
00:03:02,660 --> 00:03:04,500
Go pet your cat somewhere else.

38
00:03:04,780 --> 00:03:06,910
Were it not for the sake of your father,

39
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:09,030
I'd mess with you, too.

40
00:03:10,220 --> 00:03:12,210
Your lackeys with their barking habits

41
00:03:12,210 --> 00:03:13,600
haven't changed a bit.

42
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:17,780
If you're here today for chitchat,

43
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:18,990
I'm totally up for that.

44
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:20,340
But tell your men

45
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:22,220
to stop running their mouths

46
00:03:22,220 --> 00:03:23,680
and bringing up my father.

47
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:25,960
He gambles and parties like you guys,

48
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,690
but I'm a law-abiding citizen.

49
00:03:27,990 --> 00:03:29,750
Cutting me some slack for his sake is

50
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,210
completely unnecessary.

51
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:35,430
What are you looking at?

52
00:03:39,390 --> 00:03:40,520
You fix cars, right?

53
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:42,610
I'll fix them for you!

54
00:03:42,610 --> 00:03:43,370
Your hands!

55
00:03:47,380 --> 00:03:48,100
Hands off.

56
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:48,960
What?

57
00:03:49,450 --> 00:03:50,980
Is this your family's shop?

58
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:52,440
You got that right.

59
00:03:59,390 --> 00:03:59,790
I...

60
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:00,700
What?

61
00:04:01,270 --> 00:04:03,280
So Wanji Garage will start
hitting women now?

62
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,340
If you have any problem, come at me.

63
00:04:04,340 --> 00:04:05,270
Come at me.

64
00:04:07,270 --> 00:04:07,770
Move aside.

65
00:04:07,770 --> 00:04:08,490
No!

66
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:10,150
I'm livestreaming.

67
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:10,940
-It's live.
-Put your phone away!

68
00:04:10,940 --> 00:04:11,620
Put it away.

69
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:13,060
-It's live!
-Who are you pointing at? -Move!

70
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:14,590
-Put your phone away.
-It's live!

71
00:04:14,590 --> 00:04:16,829
It's live! I'm livestreaming! It's live...

72
00:04:16,829 --> 00:04:17,560
Give it to me.

73
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:18,709
Let go of me.

74
00:04:18,730 --> 00:04:19,459
Give me that.

75
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,380
You tried to smash my car
and mess with my people.

76
00:04:32,380 --> 00:04:33,100
Do you want to die?

77
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:33,909
What?

78
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:35,150
Want to try me?

79
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,650
I'm calling the police.

80
00:05:29,540 --> 00:05:30,630
This isn't over.

81
00:05:31,710 --> 00:05:32,710
I'll wait and see.

82
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:40,650
Let's go!

83
00:05:46,710 --> 00:05:47,770
Did that scare you?

84
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:48,909
You're hurt.

85
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:49,750
It's nothing.

86
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:53,030
Are you okay?

87
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:05,510
What's wrong?

88
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,690
Why didn't you call the police before?

89
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:11,300
You can consider it

90
00:06:11,470 --> 00:06:13,070
an unspoken rule of the game.

91
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:15,340
As long as no one's life is in danger,

92
00:06:15,390 --> 00:06:16,490
even if the police come,

93
00:06:16,490 --> 00:06:18,090
there isn't much they can do.

94
00:06:18,150 --> 00:06:19,350
How can they mediate?

95
00:06:19,740 --> 00:06:20,980
They settle it this time,

96
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:23,860
and we call them again next time
when there's trouble.

97
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:25,860
We can't waste their time like that.

98
00:06:27,180 --> 00:06:28,740
But judging from the way they acted,

99
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:30,590
they clearly came to cause trouble.

100
00:06:30,590 --> 00:06:32,650
And you couldn't beat them in a fight.

101
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:34,950
Have a seat.

102
00:06:38,540 --> 00:06:40,000
Let me tell you something.

103
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,540
Brandy might seem

104
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:43,880
to always bury himself in work every day,

105
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,740
but you haven't seen him
back in Shakun High School.

106
00:06:47,270 --> 00:06:48,300
Back then...

107
00:06:51,350 --> 00:06:55,030
You have no idea what he used to be like
when he was still

108
00:06:55,070 --> 00:06:55,990
called Touqi.

109
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:57,560
Not to mention these 3 guys today,

110
00:06:57,560 --> 00:07:00,910
he could even handle a dozen of them
without breaking a sweat.

111
00:07:00,910 --> 00:07:03,640
He had nothing to lose,
but others wanted to live.

112
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:05,150
Actually, with his build now,

113
00:07:05,150 --> 00:07:06,940
he could still knock down 10 guys.

114
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:09,400
It just depends
on whether he wants to fight.

115
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:11,660
When people from Wanji Garage
came to cause trouble before,

116
00:07:11,660 --> 00:07:12,830
Brandy didn't even fight back.

117
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:14,560
He just somehow sent them away.

118
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:16,470
But today,

119
00:07:19,570 --> 00:07:21,300
it was probably because of you.

120
00:07:23,910 --> 00:07:25,740
Actually, every time
those Wanji Garage guys come,

121
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:27,630
they're not really here to wreak havoc.

122
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:29,390
They just come to cause some small trouble

123
00:07:29,390 --> 00:07:31,250
and mess with Brandy's business.

124
00:07:31,470 --> 00:07:32,740
Touqi?

125
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:38,100
Is Touqi Jin Zhao?

126
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:39,590
Why was he called Touqi?

127
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:43,470
You are so sharp
at spotting the key points.

128
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:44,390
I never mentioned this.

129
00:07:44,390 --> 00:07:45,120
I know nothing about it.

130
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,780
Don't tell him I told you that.

131
00:07:55,940 --> 00:07:58,220
So why does Wanji Garage
have it in for Jin Zhao?

132
00:07:58,220 --> 00:07:59,420
Do they have a grudge?

133
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:02,510
Brandy worked
at Wanji Garage for many years

134
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:04,070
and eventually made it to senior mechanic,

135
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:06,070
in charge of quite a few apprentices.

136
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,910
But later, because of some issues,

137
00:08:07,910 --> 00:08:09,620
he decided to leave Wanji Garage.

138
00:08:09,620 --> 00:08:11,210
Iron Cock left with Brandy.

139
00:08:11,510 --> 00:08:12,980
After they both left,

140
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,030
a host of other junior mechanics

141
00:08:15,030 --> 00:08:16,710
either went to other shops
or quit altogether.

142
00:08:16,710 --> 00:08:18,710
It caused a big blow to Wanji Garage.

143
00:08:18,710 --> 00:08:19,850
Later, the two of them opened this shop,

144
00:08:19,850 --> 00:08:21,710
and many old clients followed them here.

145
00:08:21,710 --> 00:08:22,850
If you were one of Wanji Garage,

146
00:08:22,850 --> 00:08:24,450
would you let him off easily?

147
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:26,490
After all, when Brandy was there,

148
00:08:26,830 --> 00:08:27,660
Wanji Garage's business was

149
00:08:27,660 --> 00:08:28,860
really thriving.

150
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:52,820
Is Jin Zhao

151
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:56,490
involved in some dangerous activities?

152
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,550
What do you mean?

153
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:00,870
Things that threaten his life.

154
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:06,150
Underground fighting?

155
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:07,780
And street racing

156
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,890
with a dangerous crowd.

157
00:09:13,030 --> 00:09:14,820
I think you know a bit too much.

158
00:09:15,370 --> 00:09:16,910
What other details do you know?

159
00:09:16,910 --> 00:09:17,270
I don't know.

160
00:09:17,270 --> 00:09:17,780
-I really have no idea.
-Tell me.

161
00:09:17,780 --> 00:09:18,460
I know nothing!

162
00:09:18,460 --> 00:09:20,520
Stop asking me. I know nothing at all!

163
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:22,500
So loud.

164
00:09:25,910 --> 00:09:27,300
If Sanlai doesn't want to talk about it,

165
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,430
I can't force him to.

166
00:09:29,940 --> 00:09:31,510
Shakun High School.

167
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:32,990
Touqi.

168
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:35,780
I must get to the bottom of it.

169
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:37,680
Brandy, Brandy.

170
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:38,940
Come give me a hand.

171
00:09:38,940 --> 00:09:40,050
Let's lift this rack first.

172
00:09:40,050 --> 00:09:41,120
-Master.
-Let me help.

173
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:41,980
Please help us.

174
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,570
Why is this so heavy?

175
00:09:49,580 --> 00:09:50,530
If you were any stronger,

176
00:09:50,530 --> 00:09:51,930
you could move the Earth.

177
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:54,500
Don't get yourself dirty. Step aside.

178
00:09:55,930 --> 00:09:58,460
Let's not
talk about moving the Earth for now.

179
00:09:59,210 --> 00:09:59,930
Pardon?

180
00:10:00,330 --> 00:10:02,640
I said you're underestimating me.

181
00:10:04,330 --> 00:10:05,860
Come on. Put it down slowly.

182
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,760
I wouldn't dare underestimate you.

183
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:27,600
Come with me.

184
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:35,090
I have an important task for you.

185
00:10:35,090 --> 00:10:36,150
Pick up the screws.

186
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:43,440
Come on.

187
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,000
Let's lift this first.

188
00:11:15,060 --> 00:11:16,370
One, two, three, up!

189
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:04,840
Mu,

190
00:12:05,090 --> 00:12:06,350
they need to be sorted.

191
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:15,820
Yang,

192
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:17,680
does he look down on me?

193
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:19,150
No, not at all.

194
00:12:19,420 --> 00:12:21,180
Picking up screws is quite a hard job.

195
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:22,700
Like me, I have
no fingerprints on my hands.

196
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,100
I just can't pick them up.

197
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:07,950
A Wankel engine in a pickup for home use.

198
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:10,920
Interesting.

199
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:15,150
Send me this address.

200
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:23,640
[Pet Home]

201
00:14:00,950 --> 00:14:01,980
Hello.

202
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:05,940
Can I help you?

203
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:08,010
You can speak Chinese.

204
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:09,940
Speak Chinese?

205
00:14:10,430 --> 00:14:11,890
I thought you were a local.

206
00:14:11,990 --> 00:14:13,590
I am indeed a local.

207
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:16,060
Your Chinese is pretty good then.

208
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:17,920
Tell me what you would like to see.

209
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:18,660
Cars.

210
00:14:18,810 --> 00:14:19,640
Cars?

211
00:14:21,270 --> 00:14:22,200
Perfect timing.

212
00:14:22,210 --> 00:14:22,850
We just

213
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:24,230
got two new models.

214
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:25,940
One is a convertible like this.

215
00:14:25,940 --> 00:14:27,600
This one comes with a mesh bag.

216
00:14:27,660 --> 00:14:29,180
But we only have these two colors.

217
00:14:29,180 --> 00:14:30,380
Which one do you want?

218
00:14:30,910 --> 00:14:32,710
Racing cars for mountain roads.

219
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,030
R-Racing cars?

220
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:36,160
We don't have racing cars for pets here.

221
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:37,160
Last Saturday,

222
00:14:37,580 --> 00:14:39,510
the 15th, at 11 o'clock at night,

223
00:14:39,860 --> 00:14:40,730
where were you?

224
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:44,420
Last Saturday?

225
00:14:44,820 --> 00:14:46,110
At night?

226
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:49,540
-Did Jin Zhao mess with anyone again?
-The CCTV caught

227
00:14:49,540 --> 00:14:51,680
a black RX7.

228
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:53,350
It wasn't me.

229
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:55,150
Do you have any evidence?

230
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:56,750
Was my face caught on camera?

231
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:01,150
Actually, we didn't get a clear face shot.

232
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:02,820
No face shot means no evidence.

233
00:15:02,820 --> 00:15:03,960
Don't falsely accuse the innocent.

234
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,110
We just have these two cars
for you to buy.

235
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:05,870
If you don't want any,

236
00:15:05,870 --> 00:15:08,000
see the entrance there? You can leave.

237
00:15:15,660 --> 00:15:18,210
Is that car at the entrance yours?

238
00:15:19,540 --> 00:15:20,740
What's your problem?

239
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:25,460
A pickup truck specifically used
by a pet shop

240
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:26,660
to transport animals

241
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:29,040
with 1,000 HP, 2,000 torque,

242
00:15:29,940 --> 00:15:31,870
mounted with a Wankel engine,

243
00:15:32,020 --> 00:15:35,270
can run even faster
than supercars on the track.

244
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:42,020
1,000 HP, 2,000 torque,

245
00:15:42,230 --> 00:15:43,430
with a Wankel engine.

246
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,290
What do you mean?

247
00:15:47,540 --> 00:15:50,030
It can run even faster
than supercars on the track.

248
00:15:50,030 --> 00:15:52,290
He said the exact same thing Brandy said.

249
00:15:54,570 --> 00:15:56,610
You've got good taste, bro.

250
00:15:57,780 --> 00:15:58,540
That car is

251
00:15:59,060 --> 00:15:59,860
indeed mine.

252
00:16:00,540 --> 00:16:01,630
Why didn't you

253
00:16:01,810 --> 00:16:04,670
turn on your headlights
before the bend that night?

254
00:16:04,850 --> 00:16:08,180
Brandy was caught driving at night
with the headlights off?

255
00:16:10,630 --> 00:16:13,430
Have you heard
of the Racing Legend of Mount Akina?

256
00:16:14,180 --> 00:16:15,810
About the Japanese mountain rally racing?

257
00:16:15,810 --> 00:16:17,090
I'm not boasting.

258
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:20,180
I'm the Racing Legend of Chinatown.

259
00:16:20,710 --> 00:16:21,730
If you don't mind,

260
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:23,050
just call me Lord Sanlai

261
00:16:23,050 --> 00:16:24,400
like everyone else.

262
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,480
Was it really you that night?

263
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:38,540
Bro,

264
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:41,390
you're asking too many questions.

265
00:16:42,030 --> 00:16:42,990
But that's okay.

266
00:16:43,390 --> 00:16:44,030
Here,

267
00:16:45,230 --> 00:16:46,150
a gold card for 1 question

268
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,100
and a platinum card for 3.

269
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:47,960
Take your pick.

270
00:16:51,850 --> 00:16:52,760
Platinum card.

271
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:55,060
Very classy.

272
00:16:55,350 --> 00:16:57,750
Ask whatever you want.
I'll go register it.

273
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,340
Excuse me.

274
00:17:03,260 --> 00:17:06,020
When will this bird come down?

275
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:10,050
That's not a bird. That's my little sun.

276
00:17:11,910 --> 00:17:12,910
Excuse me.

277
00:17:13,210 --> 00:17:15,500
When will your two little suns

278
00:17:15,990 --> 00:17:18,579
ever come down?

279
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:20,050
They quite like you.

280
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:21,710
My little suns

281
00:17:21,740 --> 00:17:23,310
prefer classy people.

